### ARTICLE IV: MODIFICATIONS AND DERIVATIVES

4.1 PERMITTED ALTERATIONS: Licensee may perform modifications to the Assets 
    for legitimate use purposes, specifically including:
    (a) CLEAN EDITS: Normalization, Trimming, Fading, Equalization, 
        and Dynamic Range Compression;
    (b) CREATIVE EDITS: Filtering, Reverb, Delay, Granular Synthesis, 
        Time-stretching, and Pitch-shifting;
    (c) CONTEXTUAL INTEGRATION: Layering, Blending, and Remixing with 
        original content created by the Licensee.

4.2 OWNERSHIP OF DERIVATIVES: All derivative works remain subject to the 
    original copyright and intellectual property rights of ERRORwhately. 
    Specifically:
    (a) Licensee may own the "Composition," "Arrangement," or "Creative 
        Execution" of their project;
    (b) Licensee shall NOT own the underlying "Source Audio" or claim 
        independent copyright over the modified Assets;
    (c) The original copyright notice must be retained and visible in 
        all derivative works and related documentation.

4.3 DERIVATIVE WORK RESTRICTIONS: Licensee shall not license, sublicense, 
    or transfer any rights to Derivative Works to third parties without 
    explicit written consent from the Licensor.

