    (c) Removal, alteration, or concealment of copyright notices and 
        watermarks;
    (d) Distribution through prohibited commercial marketplaces without 
        authorization;
    (e) Misrepresentation of Asset origin or authorship.

6.2 REMEDIES: Upon discovery of breach, Licensor may:
    (a) Provide written notice allowing Licensee a cure period of 14 days 
        to remedy the violation;
    (b) Demand immediate cessation of all unauthorized activities;
    (c) Require certification of compliance with this License.

6.3 TERMINATION: If Licensee fails to cure a material breach within the 
    specified timeframe, Licensor may terminate this License immediately 
    upon written notice. Upon termination, Licensee must:
    (a) Delete all copies of the Assets from all systems and devices;
    (b) Cease distribution of any works containing the Assets;
    (c) Provide written certification of compliance within 30 days;
    (d) Remain liable for any ongoing use discovered after termination.

6.4 SURVIVAL: Articles VI, VII, VIII, and IX shall survive termination 
    of this License.

